frameDefinitions: A Figure is characterized as near the Ground, according to some contextually given scale.

A Figure is located relative to a (presumably more easily located) Ground, asserting that the Figure lies (approximately) on line from the Ground whose direction is established by semantic types of the particular LUs.
A Figure is (stably) located with respect to a Ground in terms of how the distance between them compares to some general or contextually relevant scale.
An Entity stands out perceptually in comparison to other members of its type.
A Perceiver determines the Location of a Sought_entity within a Ground.
A Figure is located relative to a Ground location.
frameExamples: She put her shoes <t>under</t> the table .
The plane landed 10 miles due <t>north</t> of Lake Travis in an empty field .
Pilot Mountain in NC is very <t>prominent</t>.
Kim <t>found</t> his hat on the far side.
